article.headline: William &amp, Mary 74, Norfolk St. 58
article.story: WILLIAMSBURG, Va. -- Danny Sumner scored 24 points and David Schneider added 20 to pace William & Mary to a 74-58 victory Wednesday night over nearby Norfolk State. William & Mary (1-2), won its home opener by making 63.2 percent (12 of 19) of its shots from the floor in the second half, including 5 of 10 3-pointers. That counteracted a career-high 32 points from Norfolk State's Michael Deloach, who scored 23 of the Spartans' 38 second-half points. Leading by 11 at halftime, the Tribe opened the second half with a 19-2 run. Norfolk State (1-1) cut the lead to 12 with 1:08 left on a Deloach 3-pointer, but could pull no closer. Brandon Monroe added 10 points and nine rebounds for Norfolk State. The teams, which are only about 50 miles apart, had met only once before, with William & Mary winning 72-56 in 1982.
